Explanation of the KMP Algorithm:
The Knuth-Morris-Pratt (KMP) Algorithm is a string searching algorithm that efficiently finds occurrences of a pattern within a text. It works by precomputing a prefix array that indicates the longest proper prefix of the pattern that is also a suffix. This information allows the algorithm to skip unnecessary comparisons when a mismatch occurs, making it more efficient than naive string searching algorithms.

